    <div class="container">
        <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
        <p>
            Here are some common questions and answers to help you navigate the SAAHAS platform effectively. 
            If you have further inquiries, feel free to contact us!
        </p>

        <div class="faq-section">
            <details>
                <summary>Is this platform free to use?</summary>
                <p>Some services like accessing information are free. However, professional services such as counseling, legal advice, and medical consultations may involve a fee.</p>
            </details>

            <details>
                <summary>How will this app help victims of domestic violence?</summary>
                <p>The app provides victims with a safe space to get information about their rights, talk to counselors, get legal advice if needed, and even seek medical help if they have physical injuries.</p>
            </details>

            <details>
                <summary>What if the counselor cannot help with my situation?</summary>
                <p>If the counselor is unable to resolve the issue, they can refer you to a legal advisor or a doctor, depending on the situation, ensuring you receive the appropriate support.</p>
            </details>

            <details>
                <summary>How can I trust the professionals on the platform?</summary>
                <p>All professionals, including counselors, legal advisors, and doctors, are required to submit their qualifications, certifications, and experience for verification before they can offer services on the platform.</p>
            </details>

            <details>
                <summary>What is meant by SAAHAS?</summary>
                <p>SAAHAS stands for Support, Advocacy, Awareness, Health, Assistance, and Safety. It represents the core values and services we offer to help individuals facing domestic violence.</p>
            </details>

            <details>
                <summary>How do I get started with the platform?</summary>
                <p>You can get started by registering an account as a Victim, Counselor, Legal Advisor, or Doctor. Each role has different features and services. Visit the Sign Up page to begin.</p>
            </details>
        </div>
